        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 19 at 11:43PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1142 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Norman, or 13 miles south of Mount Ida, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bonnerdale...                     Sunshine...
Lodi...                           Royal...
Point Cedar...                    Fancyhill...
Hempwallace...                    Norman...
Black Springs...                  Salem in Pike County...
Glenwood...                       Crystal Springs Landing...
Meyers...                         Welsh...
Rosboro...                        Lofton...
Rockwell...                       Silver...
Pettyview...                      Hopper...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for central,
western and southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
